ZH: 我很生气，因为他们没告诉我真相。
EN: I am angry because they didn't tell me the truth.

ZH: 别生气了，看开点。
EN: Don't be angry, look on the bright side.

ZH: 你为什么生气? 发生了什么事？
EN: Why are you angry? What happened?

ZH: 我生气极了，他们居然不理我。
EN: I am extremely angry, they actually ignored me.

ZH: 她的脸红红的，显然很生气。
EN: Her face was red, obviously angry.

ZH: 别跟她生气，她只是在生气的时候说了些不该说的话。
EN: Don't be angry with her, she just said something she shouldn't have when she was angry.

ZH: 生气只会让你的情绪变差。
EN: Being angry will only make your mood worse.

ZH: 我不知道我应该生气还是感激。
EN: I don't know if I should be angry or grateful.

ZH: 我家人太爱生气了，整天吵吵闹闹的。
EN: My family is too prone to anger, they argue all day long.

ZH: 生气是一种消耗精力的情绪。
EN: Anger is an emotion that consumes energy.

ZH: 如果你生气，先深呼吸，再冷静思考。
EN: If you are angry, take a deep breath, and then think calmly.

ZH: 生气可能会害了你的健康。
EN: Being angry could harm your health.

ZH: 我反而生气自己没留意这点。
EN: I am angry at myself for not paying attention to that.

ZH: 生气是一种不好的情绪。
EN: Anger is a negative emotion.

ZH: 我真的很生气，但我不知道该怎么办。
EN: I am really angry, but I don't know what to do.

ZH: 生气是一种正常的情绪反应。
EN: Anger is a normal emotional reaction.

ZH: 我实在太生气了，简直无法忍受。
EN: I am so angry, I can't bear it.

ZH: 你这样做只会让对方更生气。
EN: Doing this will only make the other person angrier.

ZH: 他昨天生气地关上了房门。
EN: He angrily slammed the door shut yesterday.

ZH: 不要跟朋友生气，很快就会和好的。
EN: Don't be angry with your friends, you will make up soon.

ZH: 生气是一种消极的情绪。
EN: Anger is a negative emotion.
